<% content_for(:page_header) do %>
<header id="page_header">
<h1>
<% if content_for?(:header_title_override) %>
<%= yield :header_title_override %>
<% else %>
<%= yield :title %>
<% end %>
</h1>
<div id="top-matter">
<% if SITE_KIND == :devel %>
<p>
<strong><u><span style="font-size:large;">THIS IS A DEVELOPMENT INSTANCE FOR THE PPC BOARD.</span></u></strong>
</p>
<% elsif SITE_KIND == :rp %>
<p>
This is the RP and backup Board for the Protectors of the Plot Continuum. <strong>Our main board is at</strong> <a href="https://www.plotprotectors.org/">https://www.plotprotectors.org/</a>
</p>
<% end %>
<p>
  Welcome, fans of the Protectors of the Plot Continuum and supporters of the Canon Protection Initiative!
  If you've got a story to plug, an opinion to share, or a discussion you want to join in, this is the place!
</p>
<p>
If you're looking for PPC stories to read, why not start with <strong><a href="https://plotprotectors.neocities.org/TOS/">The Original Series</a></strong> &ndash; the missions of the famous assassins Jay and Acacia, the very first stories in PPC history.
Once you've finished them, check out <a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/Killed_Badfic">the list of Killed Badfic</a>
to find a mission you like the look of, or <a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/The_Complete_List_of_PPC_Fiction">The Complete List of PPC Fiction</a> to look up specific agents or departments.
</p>
<p>
Before you join the fun, there are some <strong>important links</strong> you should know about.
Being familiar with these will save you a lot of hassle!
</p>

<p>
  <ul><li><a href="https://ppc.fandom.com/wiki/PPC_Constitution">The PPC Constitution</a> is Da Rules for our community.
      <strong>Read this first</strong>, read it often, and follow it.</li></ul>
</p>
<p>
  <ul>
    <% if SITE_KIND == :main %>
    <li><strong>The Board</strong> is where you are right now! There is an <a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/FAQ:_The_Board">FAQ: The Board</a> to help you learn to use it.</li>
    <% else %>
    <li><a href="https://www.plotprotectors.org/">The Board</a> is one of the main PPC community spaces. If you're new, you'll want to introduce yourself there.</li>
    <% end %>
  <li><a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/PPC_Lounge">The PPC Lounge</a> is the place for real-time chat.
    Pop in and see if anyone's around.</li>
<li><a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/PPC_Wiki">Our shiny PPC Wiki</a> will answer many of your questions.
<strong>Check before asking!</strong>
We like it when people do the research.</li>
<li>If you've got a question about the PPC or the Community, it might be Frequently Asked! Check out our FAQs:
<a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/FAQ:_For_Newbies">For Newbies</a>, <a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/Permission">On Permission</a>
, <a href="http://ppc.wikia.com/wiki/FAQ:_For_Other_People">For Other People</a>.
</li>
</ul>
</p>
</div>

